==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Maturity
<hw>Ma*tu"ri*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>maturitas</ets>: cf. F. <ets>maturit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The state or quality of being mature; ripeness; full
development; <as>as, the <ex>maturity</ex> of corn or of grass;
<ex>maturity</ex> of judgment; the <ex>maturity</ex> of a
plan.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Arrival of the time fixed for payment; a becoming
due; termination of the period a note, etc., has to run.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Matutinal</ent>⟦br⟧
